  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIf your truffle config contains an error in the RPC endpoint, the migrate command fails silently.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nthis was my config, using env variables for the sensitive stuff. I had prefixed my infura key with `v3/` so the final URL ended up being `https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/v3/...`. This caused my deployed to fail but gave no error or information about why. If the endpoint fails there should be some kind of error bubbling up. \r\n\r\n```\r\n    mainnet: {\r\n      provider() {\r\n        return new HDWalletProvider(\r\n          process.env.ENS_MAINNET,\r\n          'https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/' + process.env.INFURA_API_KEY\r\n        )\r\n      },\r\n      network_id: 1,\r\n      gasPrice: 1000000000 * 6\r\n    },\r\n```\r\nThis could also be an error with HDWalletProvider. I'm using the new truffle and the new HDWalltProvider. Versions are below.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nExpect to see an error when the URL fails\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNo Error message. Just a silent fail.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n*  truffle-hdwallet-provider: \"^1.0.0-web3one.0\",\r\n* Operating System: \r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): v5.0.0-beta.1 (core: 5.0.0-beta.1),  0.4.25 (solc-js)\r\n* node version (`node --version`): v8.10.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`):  5.6.0\r\n",
